    "media:imagetext": "THE SATURDAY EVENING POST\nSuper-6\nCLIPPER\nN65260\nPAA\nPAA\nPAA\nYou fly with the world's most experienced airline\nwhen you so overseas ran am\nThis family of five will save $1,000\nusing Pan Am's Family Plan to Europe\nNow a family vacation in Europe is in reach\nof thousands to whom it has never been more\nthan a hope. Pan Am's new Family Plan-plus\ntheir money-saving Rainbow Clipper* tourist\nservice, with the convenience of their original\n\"Pay-Later\" Plan-takes it out of the dream class.\nIt works this way for the family of five\nshown above-on a trip between New York Children under twelve go for half Dad's fare.\nand Paris. They go during Thrift Season\nNo restrictions. You go when you choose,\n(November 1 to March 31) when fares are al-\nand the whole trip can be budgeted over 20\nways lower, and Dad benefits by a round-trip\nmonths with Pan Am's \"Pay-Later\" Plan. See\nfare of only $518. Mother, and each youngster\nyour Travel Agent now, or call Pan American.\nbetween 12 and 25, pay the Family Plan rate\n•Trade-Mark Reg. U.S. Pat. Of.\nof $318 each. The total saving, for 5, is $1000.\nPAN AMERICAN WORLD\nAIRWAYS",
